<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="utf-8">
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width,initial-scale=1">
<meta name="robots" content="index,follow">
<meta name="description" content="Daily LLM-generated diary for the 273 Ventures KAOS open-source ecosystem. Compliance-flavored rolling summary of the last 24 hours of git activity.">
<base href="{{ base_href | default('/kaos-compliance/') }}">
<title>Daily diary — KAOS Compliance</title>
{#
  Expected data shape:
  {
    "diary": {
      "generated_at": "2026-05-11T15:00:00Z",
      "narrative": "...",
      "notable_items": ["..."],
      "end_user_changes": ["..."],
      "risk_callouts": ["..."],
      "repos_observed": 17,
      "commit_count": 23,
      "date": "2026-05-11",
      "model": "claude-sonnet-4-6",
      "cost_usd": 0.0123
    },
    "history": [
      {"date": "2026-05-10", "narrative_excerpt": "...", "commit_count": 18, "href": "..."},
      ...
    ]
  }
#}
<style>
:root{
 --s-1:4px;--s-2:8px;--s-3:12px;--s-4:16px;--s-5:24px;--s-6:32px;--s-7:48px;
 --page-bg:#fff;--card-bg:#fafbfc;--border:#e5e7eb;--text:#111827;--muted:#6b7280;
 --g-bg:#e6f4ea;--g-fg:#1e7e34;--y-bg:#fff8e1;--y-fg:#8a6d00;
 --r-bg:#fdecea;--r-fg:#b42318;--n-bg:#f3f4f6;--n-fg:#4b5563;
 --focus:#2563eb;
 --mono:ui-monospace,"SF Mono",Menlo,Consolas,"Liberation Mono",monospace;
 --sans:-apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,"Segoe UI",Roboto,"Helvetica Neue",Arial,sans-serif;
}
@media (prefers-color-scheme: dark){
 :root{--page-bg:#0b0f14;--card-bg:#11161d;--border:#1f2937;--text:#e5e7eb;--muted:#9ca3af;
  --g-bg:#14271b;--g-fg:#4ade80;--y-bg:#2a2410;--y-fg:#facc15;
  --r-bg:#2a1414;--r-fg:#f87171;--n-bg:#1f2937;--n-fg:#9ca3af;--focus:#60a5fa;}
}
*{box-sizing:border-box}
html,body{margin:0;padding:0;background:var(--page-bg);color:var(--text);font-family:var(--sans);font-size:16px;line-height:1.5}
a{color:var(--focus);text-decoration:underline;text-underline-offset:2px}
a:focus-visible{outline:2px solid var(--focus);outline-offset:2px;border-radius:2px}
.wrap{max-width:1200px;margin:0 auto;padding:var(--s-7) var(--s-5)}
.page-head{display:flex;justify-content:space-between;align-items:baseline;flex-wrap:wrap;gap:var(--s-3);border-bottom:1px solid var(--border);padding-bottom:var(--s-4);margin-bottom:var(--s-6)}
.page-head h1{margin:0;font-size:2rem;line-height:1.1}
.page-head p{margin:var(--s-1) 0 0;color:var(--muted);font-size:0.875rem}
.page-head .meta{font-family:var(--mono);font-size:0.75rem;color:var(--muted)}
nav.subnav{margin-top:var(--s-3);display:flex;gap:var(--s-4);flex-wrap:wrap;font-size:0.875rem}
nav.subnav a{color:var(--muted)}
nav.subnav a.methodology{font-weight:600;color:var(--text);border-bottom:1px dotted var(--text)}
h2{font-size:1.5rem;line-height:1.25;margin:var(--s-6) 0 var(--s-3);font-weight:600}
h3{font-size:1.125rem;line-height:1.25;margin:var(--s-5) 0 var(--s-2);font-weight:600}
.card{background:var(--card-bg);border:1px solid var(--border);border-radius:6px;padding:var(--s-5)}
.strip{display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(4,1fr);gap:var(--s-4);margin-bottom:var(--s-5)}
.strip .stat{background:var(--card-bg);border:1px solid var(--border);border-radius:6px;padding:var(--s-3) var(--s-4)}
.strip .stat .n{font-family:var(--mono);font-size:1.75rem;font-weight:700;line-height:1.1;display:block}
.strip .stat .lab{color:var(--muted);font-size:0.75rem;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:0.04em}
.narrative{font-size:1rem;line-height:1.65;color:var(--text);margin:0}
.narrative p{margin:0 0 var(--s-3)}
.lists{display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr;gap:var(--s-5);margin-top:var(--s-5)}
.lists section{background:var(--card-bg);border:1px solid var(--border);border-radius:6px;padding:var(--s-4)}
.lists section h3{margin:0 0 var(--s-2);font-size:0.9375rem;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:0.04em;color:var(--muted)}
.lists ul{margin:0;padding-left:var(--s-5);font-size:0.9375rem}
.lists li{margin-bottom:var(--s-1)}
.lists .empty{color:var(--muted);font-style:italic;font-size:0.875rem;margin:0}
.lists .risk h3{color:var(--r-fg)}
.lists .risk{border-color:var(--r-fg)}
.history{margin-top:var(--s-5);display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:var(--s-3)}
.history .day{background:var(--card-bg);border:1px solid var(--border);border-radius:6px;padding:var(--s-4)}
.history .day .when{font-family:var(--mono);font-size:0.8125rem;color:var(--muted);display:flex;justify-content:space-between;gap:var(--s-3);margin-bottom:var(--s-2)}
.history .day p{margin:0;font-size:0.9375rem;color:var(--text)}
.history .day a{font-family:var(--mono);font-size:0.75rem}
.banner{background:var(--y-bg);color:var(--y-fg);border:1px solid var(--y-fg);border-radius:6px;padding:var(--s-3) var(--s-4);margin-bottom:var(--s-5);font-size:0.875rem}
.banner strong{font-weight:700}
footer{margin-top:var(--s-7);padding-top:var(--s-4);border-top:1px solid var(--border);color:var(--muted);font-size:0.75rem;font-family:var(--mono)}
footer a{color:var(--muted)}
.skip{position:absolute;left:-9999px}
.skip:focus{position:static;display:inline-block;padding:var(--s-2);background:var(--y-bg);color:var(--y-fg)}
/* R21: dedicated visually-hidden utility for strict-CSP-compatible
   off-screen headings (no inline ``style``). Mirrors the .sr-only
   pattern on the index template. */
.sr-only{position:absolute;width:1px;height:1px;padding:0;margin:-1px;overflow:hidden;clip:rect(0,0,0,0);white-space:nowrap;border:0}
@media (max-width:720px){
 .wrap{padding:var(--s-5) var(--s-4)}
 .page-head h1{font-size:1.5rem}
 .strip{grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr}
 .lists{grid-template-columns:1fr}
}
@media print{
 :root{--page-bg:#fff;--card-bg:#fff;--text:#000;--muted:#444;--border:#999}
 a{color:#000;text-decoration:none}
 .wrap{padding:0;max-width:none}
 .card,.strip .stat,.history .day,.lists section{box-shadow:none}
 nav.subnav,.skip{display:none}
}
</style>
</head>
<body>
<a class="skip" href="#main">Skip to content</a>
<div class="wrap">
<header class="page-head">
 <div>
  <h1>Daily diary</h1>
  <p>LLM-generated rolling summary of the last 24h of git activity across the KAOS open-source ecosystem. Auditor view; see <a href="methodology.html">methodology</a> for limits.</p>
  <nav class="subnav" aria-label="Sections">
   <a href="index.html">Org rollup</a>
   <a href="methodology.html" class="methodology">Methodology</a>
   <a href="security.html">Security</a>
   <a href="supply-chain.html">Supply chain</a>
   <a href="governance.html">Governance</a>
  </nav>
 </div>
 <div class="meta" aria-label="Last generated">
  Generated {{ generated_at_display | default('—') }}
 </div>
</header>

<main id="main">

{% set d = diary | default({}) %}
{# R12: when the diary has no data yet (cold start, first sweep, or LLM
   provider unavailable), make absolutely clear that this is an active
   feature with a defined contract — not an abandoned page. The empty
   state previously read as "feature shipped, then forgotten"; we now
   surface the cron cadence + LLM-availability contract up front. #}
{% set has_narrative = (d.narrative is defined and d.narrative and not d.skipped) %}

{% if d.skipped %}
<div class="banner" role="status">
 <strong>Diary unavailable for this window.</strong>
 {{ d.skipped_reason | default('No LLM call was made for this window.') }}
 Commit aggregation below is still authoritative; the daily narrative
 will resume on the next sweep when the model-provider API key is wired
 (see <a href="methodology.html#cadence">methodology &mdash; cadence</a>).
</div>
{% elif not has_narrative and not (history | default([])) %}
<div class="banner" role="status">
 <strong>Diary cold start.</strong>
 The diary collector runs on the 24h Full sweep (see
 <a href="methodology.html#cadence">methodology &mdash; cadence</a>) and
 publishes one entry per UTC day. This page populates after the first
 successful sweep; until then the headline counts and per-package detail
 pages remain the evidence path.
</div>
{% endif %}

<section aria-labelledby="strip-h">
 <h2 id="strip-h" class="sr-only">Headline counts</h2>
 <div class="strip">
  <div class="stat"><span class="n">{{ d.date | default('—') }}</span><span class="lab">Diary date (UTC)</span></div>
  <div class="stat"><span class="n">{{ d.repos_observed | default('—') }}</span><span class="lab">Repos observed</span></div>
  <div class="stat"><span class="n">{{ d.repos_with_changes | default('—') }}</span><span class="lab">Repos with changes</span></div>
  <div class="stat"><span class="n">{{ d.commit_count | default(0) }}</span><span class="lab">Commits in window</span></div>
 </div>
</section>

<section aria-labelledby="narr-h">
 <h2 id="narr-h">Narrative</h2>
 <div class="card">
  {% set narrative = d.narrative | default('No narrative is available for this window. The collector emitted no LLM output, or the model returned an unparseable response. See the methodology page for the diary contract.') %}
  <p class="narrative">{{ narrative }}</p>
 </div>
</section>

<section aria-labelledby="lists-h">
 <h2 id="lists-h">Highlights</h2>
 <div class="lists">
  <section aria-labelledby="notable-h">
   <h3 id="notable-h">Notable items</h3>
   {% set notable = d.notable_items | default([]) %}
   {% if notable %}
    <ul>
     {% for item in notable %}<li>{{ item }}</li>{% endfor %}
    </ul>
   {% else %}
    <p class="empty">No notable items recorded for this window.</p>
   {% endif %}
  </section>

  <section aria-labelledby="enduser-h">
   <h3 id="enduser-h">End-user-facing changes</h3>
   {% set enduser = d.end_user_changes | default([]) %}
   {% if enduser %}
    <ul>
     {% for item in enduser %}<li>{{ item }}</li>{% endfor %}
    </ul>
   {% else %}
    <p class="empty">No downstream-visible changes were surfaced for this window.</p>
   {% endif %}
  </section>

  <section class="risk" aria-labelledby="risk-h">
   <h3 id="risk-h">Risk callouts</h3>
   {% set risks = d.risk_callouts | default([]) %}
   {% if risks %}
    <ul>
     {% for item in risks %}<li>{{ item }}</li>{% endfor %}
    </ul>
   {% else %}
    <p class="empty">No risk callouts were surfaced for this window.</p>
   {% endif %}
  </section>

  <section aria-labelledby="prov-h">
   <h3 id="prov-h">Provenance</h3>
   <ul>
    <li>Model: <code>{{ d.model | default('—') }}</code></li>
    <li>Generated at: <code>{{ d.generated_at | default('—') }}</code></li>
    <li>Cutoff: <code>{{ d.cutoff_iso | default('—') }}</code></li>
    {% if d.cost_usd is not none and d.cost_usd is defined %}
    <li>Prompt cost: <code>${{ '%.4f' | format(d.cost_usd) }}</code></li>
    {% endif %}
    {% if d.artifact_path %}
    <li>Artifact: <a href="{{ d.artifact_path }}"><code>{{ d.artifact_path }}</code></a></li>
    {% endif %}
   </ul>
  </section>
 </div>
</section>

<section aria-labelledby="hist-h">
 <h2 id="hist-h">Recent days</h2>
 {% set history = history | default([]) %}
 {% if history %}
  <div class="history">
   {% for entry in history[:14] %}
   <article class="day">
    <div class="when">
     <span>{{ entry.date }}</span>
     <span>
      {% if entry.commit_count is defined %}{{ entry.commit_count }} commits{% endif %}
      {% if entry.href %} &middot; <a href="{{ entry.href }}">artifact</a>{% endif %}
     </span>
    </div>
    <p>{{ entry.narrative_excerpt | default('(no excerpt)') }}</p>
   </article>
   {% endfor %}
  </div>
 {% else %}
  <div class="card">
   <p class="empty" style="margin:0;color:var(--muted)">No prior days are recorded yet. The diary accumulates one entry per UTC day; the rolling history will populate as the collector runs.</p>
  </div>
 {% endif %}
</section>

<section aria-labelledby="meta-h">
 <h2 id="meta-h">About this view</h2>
 <div class="card">
  <p style="margin:0 0 var(--s-3)">
   The diary is one LLM-generated render of the last 24 hours of git activity
   across every public <code>273v/kaos-*</code> repository the collector
   tracks. The narrative is produced by a frontier model with an
   auditor-register system prompt; the lists are the model's surfaced items,
   bounded at 12 (notable, end-user) or 6 (risk).
  </p>
  <p style="margin:0;color:var(--muted);font-size:0.875rem">
   The counts above (repos observed, commits in window) come from
   <code>git log</code> directly and are authoritative regardless of the
   model's narrative. If the narrative disagrees with the counts, trust the
   counts. The diary is a navigation aid; the per-package detail pages and
   the raw <a href="api/v1/snapshot.json">snapshot.json</a> remain the
   evidence path.
  </p>
 </div>
</section>

</main>

<footer>
 Generated {{ generated_at_display | default('—') }}
 | Source: <a href="https://github.com/273v/kaos-compliance">github.com/273v/kaos-compliance</a>
 | Methodology: <a href="methodology.html">methodology.html</a>
 | Data: <a href="api/v1/snapshot.json">snapshot.json</a>
</footer>
</div>
</body>
</html>
